content.description: Start standing, and dyno for a big jug. Pretty crumbly so be careful. Could be sat start, but would be hard due to bad rock.
content.location: Get to it by going to the second pile or rocks(the main pile), its right across from the big cave in the enclosure like area. It is kinda its own boulder. Top out and walk down backside.

content.description: Fun little overhanging v-shaped rock. Start sitting at the base with one hand out on the outside and one in the inside and work up to a big move to the lip.
content.location: Right off the road in the middle of the two main boulder piles.

content.description: Sandstone bouldering, very rough and hard on the hands.  Some holds are suspect and should be checked.  Sunny and windy in the middle of the ND prairie.  Some caves to sit start and climb out of, nice landings.  Bring spotter and pads.
